The paper discusses gradient-based learning algorithms for problems in supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning, which are all subfields of machine learning. The paper introduces the formalism of stochastic computation graphs, which are relevant to the subfield of probabilistic modeling (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions attention, memory, and control actions, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses variance-reduction techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
